data.name: Creamy Avocado and Yogurt Guacamole
data.quickTastyDescription: A refreshing twist on traditional guacamole, this creamy dip combines ripe avocados with tangy yogurt for a deliciously smooth texture.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the avocados in half, remove the pit, and scoop the flesh into a mixing bowl.
Add the Greek yogurt, lime juice, minced garlic, and cilantro to the bowl.
Mash the ingredients together until you reach your desired level of creaminess.
If using, fold in the jalapeño for a spicy kick.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh veggies.
data.modifiersForBase: Creamy and tangy with Greek yogurt
